They were very accommodating to gluten-free folks (the meats, sauces, and several sides were GF) and even brought a few fried catfish dinners for the pescatarians. Everyone loved the food and the service!

Went there for lunch because it's been my experience that most of the locally owned businesses in the area are at least very good. I wasn't wrong! Buh's has now become my go to BBQ in the Navarre area. (...and there are TWO locations!).

I got the Rib Platter (6 ribs) instead of the Rib plate (3 ribs) in case the ribs were short ones. Well, they were definitely NOT short. I had to (reluctantly) share some with my dining mates. I love sweet potato fries and have never found the need to dip them in anything. Buh's fries certainly don't NEED dipping sauce. But the sweet dipping sauce is so good that I NEEDED the fries to scrape out every drop from the container.

Update: 3/12/2025  I went back again today for lunch. This time I ordered the 3 rib plate, knowing I couldn't finish 6. Well imagine my surprise after I finished my first rib, there were still 3 on the plate!

I was still only able to finish two of the four. Where else can you go and eat 2/3rd's of what you ordered and still have 2/3rd's left on the plate?

Try Buh's. You will never be disappointed.

detailedReviews.author: Courtney Billings
detailedReviews.text: I was really excited to try this place... When we walked in, I immediately felt bad for the waitress because it was just her with a full house. We ordered the daily special:  sandwich and two sides. I got the Mac n cheese and baked beans. They tasted the same because there was sooooo much pepper, I couldn't even eat them. Only ate my sandwich (which was good!) Then my friend went to take a bite of his sandwich and there was the twist tie from the sandwich bag embedded on the bottom bun. I went snacking on the fried pickles we ordered, and there was a dark brown/black piece of hair. I was immediately done after that. The waitress asked if everything was OK, I said no, we would just like the check. She walked over to the register and said she could take us there. I told her I wasn't mad at her, but just wanted to go. I let her know what happened, and she made a questionable face and said "well the managers will be here tomorrow, so I'll let them know." She didn't go look at all. Made me feel like I was lying about it. It was very rude and hurtful. Especially because I was trying to be calm and subtle about everything. Paid over $50 for 2 people (3 in my party) to eat 2 sandwiches. Absolutely horrible experience

positive.author: Katie Spragg
positive.text: Friendly and relaxed atmosphere. Great service. We have been here three times and each time, everything we have ordered has been great!

positive.author: Heather Kingry
positive.text: Buh's catered my wedding and went above and beyond! We served brisket (yum!), a whole roasted pig presented beautifully, mashed potatoes, coleslaw and beans. They were very accommodating to gluten-free folks (the meats, sauces, and several sides were GF) and even brought a few fried catfish dinners for the pescatarians. Everyone loved the food and the service!

positive.author: Patrick Marot
positive.text: Our son recently got married in Navarre.  We had 2 days to figure out a rehearsal dinner for 40 people.  I read the positive reviews for Buh‚Äôs and decided to give them a call.  I spoke with John the owner who was extremely helpful every step of the way with catering this event.  The food arrived at the precise time we ordered it.  It was hot and delicious and plenty of food for our guests.  The price was reasonable as well. Thank you to John and the staff!  I would definitely recommend Buh‚Äôs.

neutral.text: The brisket plate tasted ok, but it was dry. I think a bit over cooked.

negative.author: Garret Tippets
negative.text: Came in and was greeted, I placed my order and tipped at the counter. Expecting the waitress to come and ask how everything was or at least offer a refill. For almost 30$ for a sandwich and some sweet potatoe fries( that were cold) on coming to my table I honestly Expected more. It would be 32 dollars to Door dash the same meal to my work. Really disappointed in the service and quality of the food during my visit.

negative.author: John Grable
negative.text: I Went there tonight July 4 2025. I am a local and have ate here countless times. My family and I are originally North Carolina residents and I spoke very highly of their food and it being like home. It was the worst experience the FOH was extremely rood and unhelpful they had every order in front of ours wrong. Honestly when I finally got our order I left knowing my family and I were just going to get whatever we were given and I was exactly right. None of our food was correct so we just opened boxes and shared our mystery dinner. They have fallen a long way since their son and served closely together in a local church and military service. He worked extremely hard and I sampled most of their products while they were being perfected. I've known this family and their sons efforts to build a great brand for many years and hope this was only a one time bad night they were having.

negative.author: Angela Davis-Coker
negative.text: Got 5 brisket sandwiches, 3 sides, and 3 key lime pies. The brisket was bland and tough, the sides were good, the key limes pies were the worst key lime pies we have ever had. All in all, I would not recommend this place to true BBQ lovers. Personally, it does not deliver the punch I was expecting. At around $15 a sandwich, I was expecting it to bring the flavor.
